### Notification System API Tests
### Use with REST Client extension in VS Code or similar tool
### Make sure to replace YOUR_TOKEN with actual JWT token

@baseUrl = http://localhost:4000/api
@token = YOUR_TOKEN

### Test 1: Get Unread Count
GET {{baseUrl}}/notifications/unread-count
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Test 2: Get All Notifications
GET {{baseUrl}}/notifications?limit=10&offset=0
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Test 3: Get Unread Notifications Only
GET {{baseUrl}}/notifications?limit=10&unreadOnly=true
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Test 4: Get Notification Preferences
GET {{baseUrl}}/notifications/preferences
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Test 5: Mark Notification as Read (replace NOTIFICATION_ID)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/notifications/NOTIFICATION_ID/read
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Test 6: Mark All Notifications as Read
POST {{baseUrl}}/notifications/mark-all-read
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Test 7: Delete Notification (replace NOTIFICATION_ID)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/notifications/NOTIFICATION_ID
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Test 8: Update Notification Preference
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/notifications/preferences
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "type": "appointment_booked",
  "channel": "email",
  "enabled": true
}

